

##### The above command is used to clone all the branches in the github
git clone --mirror <repository_url>

#####Once the cloning process is complete, navigate into the newly created directory:

cd <repository_name>.git
#####Replace <repository_name> with the name of the repository.


git branch -a
###List all the branches in the repository:

git checkout <branch_name>
####To work with a specific branch, you can check it out as follows:

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------
If you've cloned a repository using the --mirror option and you want to push it to a new repository, you can follow these steps:


git remote add new_origin <new_repository_url>


git push new_origin --all
git push new_origin --tags


git remote remove origin
###This step is optional and depends on whether you want to keep the old origin as a remote.

